title: Led Zeppelin - 1980.06.18 Cologne, Germany (Remaster)
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1980.06.18 Cologne, Germany   

Led Zeppelin
1980/06/18
Cologne Germany
Soundboard w/audience patching
Winston Remasters

SBD Source 1stGenCass>DAT2
AUD Source Master>DAT1>2CDR2

Mixed and Mastered with Samplitude. Waves Plugins used to 
Enhance the Sound.

Soundboard Source: 
Incomplete excellent soundboard recording. The recording 
is a very good balanced professional board tape.

Audience Source:
Almost complete very good audience recording. The recording 
is fairly close to the stage and has an expansive sound to 
it. The vocals push the audience tape to the edge of 
distortion but the tape holds.

Tracklist:

LZ 1980-06-18 D1T1 - The Train Kept A Rollin'
LZ 1980-06-18 D1T2 - Nobody's Fault But Mine
LZ 1980-06-18 D1T3 - Black Dog
LZ 1980-06-18 D1T4 - In The Evening
LZ 1980-06-18 D1T5 - The Rain Song
LZ 1980-06-18 D1T6 - Hot Dog
LZ 1980-06-18 D1T7 - All My Love
LZ 1980-06-18 D1T8 - Trampled Underfoot
LZ 1980-06-18 D1T9 - Since I've Been Loving You
LZ 1980-06-18 D2T1 - Achilles Last Stand
LZ 1980-06-18 D2T2 - White Summer
LZ 1980-06-18 D2T3 - Black Mountain Side
LZ 1980-06-18 D2T4 - Kashmir
LZ 1980-06-18 D2T5 - Stairway To Heaven
LZ 1980-06-18 D2T6 - Rock And Roll
LZ 1980-06-18 D2T7 - Communication Breakdown

Comments: 
Another early 1980 show that is strong and fast paced. 
The opening string of numbers is powerful and the band 
seems ready to play from the outset. Jimmy reaches for 
boredom in White Summer and the whole of Since I've Been 
Loving You is a joke for Jimmy ... he is constantly out 
of tune and out of time throughout the whole piece! 
Achilles Last Stand is excellent and the minimalistic 
encores finish off this show
